The focus of this paper involves “Coronavirus disease 2019” (known as Covid-19), which is caused by an infectious virus, “Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus 2” (known as SARS-CoV-2). The first published studies of what would become a pandemic began to be published in late January 2020, when the novel corona virus was known as 2019-nCoV (
 Chan et al., 2020; 
 Huang et al., 2020).
